    "body": "Dynamic initialization of function level static vaiables in non-thread safe code is against chromium style guide, prefer [base::LazyInstance<T>::Leaky](https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/base/lazy_instance.h?q=base::LazyInstance&sq=package:chromium&type=cs&l=82). Original chromium discussion https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/forum/#!msg/chromium-dev/p6h3HC8Wro4/o37LbEqEuoEJ .\r\n\r\nComing back to the leak referenced in this PR, it isn't actually a leak when the global variable is holding reference until the process is closed and doesn't grow, we leave the system to reclaim it."
